  "question_text": "<h3>Two Sum</h3><p>Return indices of the two numbers that add up to $target$.</p>",
  "difficulty": "EASY",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "nums, target.",
  "output_format": "[i, j].",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 10^4"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use a hash map to store seen numbers and their indices. For each number, check if $(target - num)$ is in the map.",
  "answer": "def twoSum(nums, target):\n    m = {}\n    for i, x in enumerate(nums):\n        if target - x in m: return [m[target-x], i]\n        m[x] = i",
